 Kampala, Uganda | THE INDEPENDENT | President Museveni has assured the people of Lango Sub-Region in Northern Uganda that pockets of insecurity in the area will be dealt with government. He said that since the National Resistance Movement (NRM) government had been able to deal with notorious people like Kony, Lakwena and cattle rustlers that peddled insecurity, the current situation will also be dealt with after conducting a regional security meeting. Museveni made the remarks at the Thanksgiving ceremony of Paul Amoru Omiat, Dokolo North Member of Parliament held on March 10 at Adwoki Technical Institute in Dokolo district. He was happy to note that infrastructural and personal developments in the region have taken root. He, therefore, encouraged the people of the area to keep up the efforts. The post THIS WEEK: Museveni promises to tackle crime in Lango sub-region appeared first on The Independent Uganda:. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The Independent Uganda:. Click here to read the full text on the original website.